From cou.: 22 One of the most up-to-date LCIA methods today is ReCiPe.10 The focus during the development of this method was on the compatibility of mid- and endpoint methods in terms of the assumptions that create the measures defined in the model. ReCiPe is a combination of the established CML 2002 and the Eco-Indicator 99 methods. At the midpoint-level, ReCiPe consists of the following 18 impact categories:
